## 💡 The "Action Server" Flow (Edge Case)
Sometimes, Rasa needs to talk *back* to your databases. 
If during a conversation, Rasa determines it needs to validate a phone number or check real-time availability using a custom python script, it triggers an action in `hospital_nlu.actions.actions`. 
This action server executes standard Python, talks directly to DynamoDB (bypassing FastAPI), updates the slots in Rasa's memory, and then finishes its thought.
